fields.name: pointCellCondBasedCa
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : spiking
State Variable : v (voltage)

Derived Variable : iChannels (current) = Sum[ populations[*]/i" ]
Derived Variable : iSyn" (current) = Sum[ synapses[*]/i ]
Derived Variable : iMemb (current) = iChannels + iSyn
Derived Variable : caConc (concentration) = Sum[ concentrationModels[species='ca']/concentration ]
Derived Variable : iCa (current) = Sum[ populations[ion='ca']/i ]

Time Derivative : dv/dt = iMemb / C

  v = v0
  spiking = 0

if [ v > thresh and spiking < 0.5 ]
  spiking = 1
  EventOut : spike

if [ v < thresh]
  spiking = 0

fields.name: cell
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : debugVal
State Variable : spiking
State Variable : v (voltage)

Derived Variable : totSpecCap (specificCapacitance) = biophysicalProperties/totSpecCap
Derived Variable : totCap (capacitance) = totSpecCap * surfaceArea
Derived Variable : iSyn (current) = Sum[ synapses[*]/i ]
Derived Variable : iCa (current) = biophysicalProperties/membraneProperties/iCa
Derived Variable : caConcExt (concentration) = biophysicalProperties/intracellularProperties/caConcExt
Derived Variable : initMembPot (voltage) = biophysicalProperties/membraneProperties/initMembPotential/value
Derived Variable : thresh (voltage) = biophysicalProperties/membraneProperties/spikeThresh/value
Derived Variable : caConc (concentration) = biophysicalProperties/intracellularProperties/caConc
Derived Variable : debug = biophysicalProperties/membraneProperties/totChanCurrent
Derived Variable : surfaceArea (area) = Sum[ morphology/segments[*]/surfaceArea ]
Derived Variable : iChannels (current) = biophysicalProperties/membraneProperties/totChanCurrent

Time Derivative : dv/dt= (iChannels + iSyn) / totCap

On Start
  spiking = 0
  v = initMembPot

if [ v > thresh and spiking < 0.5 ]
  spiking = 1
  EventOut ="spike

if [ v < thresh ]
  spiking = 0

if [ t >= 0 ]
  debugVal = debug
fields.description: Cell with _segment_s specified in a _morphology_ element along with details on its _biophysicalProperties_. NOTE: this can only be correctly simulated using LEMS when there is a single segment in the cell, and _v of this cell represents the membrane potential in that isopotential segment!!!

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="decayingPoolConcentrationModel" extends="concentrationModel" description="Model of buffering of concentration of an _ion (currently hard coded to be calcium, due to requirement for _iCa) which has a baseline level _restingConc and tends to this value with time course _decayConstant. The ion is assumed to occupy a shell inside the membrane of thickness _shellThickness."><Parameter name="shellThickness" dimension="length"/><Parameter name="restingConc" dimension="concentration"/><Parameter name="decayConstant" dimension="time"/><Constant name = "Faraday" value = "96485.3C_per_mol" dimension = "charge_per_mole"/><Constant name = "AREA_SCALE" value = "1m2" dimension = "area"/><Constant name = "LENGTH_SCALE" value = "1m" dimension = "length"/><Requirement name="iCa" dimension="current"/><Text name="ion"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="extConcentration" dimension="concentration" exposure="extConcentration"/><StateVariable name="concentration" dimension="concentration" exposure="concentration"/><DerivedVariable name="innerRadius" dimension="length" value="effectiveRadius - shellThickness"/><DerivedVariable name="effectiveRadius" dimension="length" value="LENGTH_SCALE * sqrt(surfaceArea/(AREA_SCALE * (4 * 3.14159)))"/><DerivedVariable name="shellVolume" dimension="volume" value="(4 * (effectiveRadius * effectiveRadius * effectiveRadius) * 3.14159 / 3) - (4 * (innerRadius * innerRadius * innerRadius) * 3.14159 / 3)"/><TimeDerivative variable="concentration" value="iCa / (2 * Faraday * shellVolume) - ((concentration - restingConc) / decayConstant)"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="concentration" value="initialConcentration"/><StateAssignment variable="extConcentration" value="initialExtConcentration"/></OnStart><OnCondition test="concentration .lt. 0"><StateAssignment variable="concentration" value="0"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: decayingPoolConcentrationModel
fields.description: Model of buffering of concentration of an _ion (currently hard coded to be calcium, due to requirement for _iCa) which has a baseline level _restingConc and tends to this value with time course _decayConstant. The ion is assumed to occupy a shell inside the membrane of thickness _shellThickness.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="iafTauRefCell" extends="iafTauCell" description="Integrate and fire cell which returns to its leak reversal potential of _leakReversal with a time course _tau. It has a refractory period of _refract after spiking"><Parameter name="refract" dimension="time"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="lastSpikeTime" dimension="time"/><StateVariable name="v" dimension="voltage" exposure="v"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="v" value="reset"/></OnStart><Regime name="refractory"><OnEntry><StateAssignment variable="lastSpikeTime" value="t"/><StateAssignment variable="v" value="reset"/></OnEntry><OnCondition test="t .gt. lastSpikeTime + refract"><Transition regime="integrating"/></OnCondition></Regime><Regime name="integrating" initial="true"><TimeDerivative variable="v" value="(leakReversal - v) / tau"/><OnCondition test="v .gt. thresh"><EventOut port="spike"/><Transition regime="refractory"/></OnCondition></Regime></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: iafTauRefCell
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable : v (voltage)
StateVariable : lastSpikeTime (time)

OnStart :
    v = leakReversal

Regime : refractory :
    OnEntry :
        lastSpikeTime = t
        v = reset
    
    if [ t > lastSpikeTime + refract ] :
        Transition : integrating

Regime : integrating (initial) :
    TimeDerivative : dv/dt = (leakReversal - v) / tau
    if [ v > thresh ] :
        EventOut : spike
        Transition : refractory
fields.description: Integrate and fire cell which returns to its leak reversal potential of _leakReversal with a time course _tau. It has a refractory period of _refract after spiking

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="adExIaFCell" extends="baseCellMembPotCap" description="Model based on Brette R and Gerstner W (2005) Adaptive Exponential Integrate-and-Fire Model as an Effective Description of Neuronal Activity. J Neurophysiol 94:3637-3642"><Parameter name="reset" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="EL" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="b" dimension="current"/><Parameter name="refract" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="thresh" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="delT" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="a" dimension="conductance"/><Parameter name="VT" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="gL" dimension="conductance"/><Parameter name="tauw" dimension="time"/><Attachments name="synapses" type="basePointCurrent"/><Exposure name="w" dimension="current"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="lastSpikeTime" dimension="time"/><StateVariable name="w" dimension="current" exposure="w"/><StateVariable name="v" dimension="voltage" exposure="v"/><DerivedVariable name="iSyn" dimension="current" exposure="iSyn" select="synapses[*]/i" reduce="add"/><DerivedVariable name="iMemb" dimension="current" exposure="iMemb" value="-1 * gL * (v - EL) + gL * delT * exp((v - VT) / delT) - w + iSyn"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="v" value="EL"/><StateAssignment variable="w" value="0"/></OnStart><Regime name="refractory"><TimeDerivative variable="w" value="(a * (v - EL) - w) / tauw"/><OnEntry><StateAssignment variable="lastSpikeTime" value="t"/><StateAssignment variable="v" value="reset"/><StateAssignment variable="w" value="w + b"/></OnEntry><OnCondition test="t .gt. lastSpikeTime + refract"><Transition regime="integrating"/></OnCondition></Regime><Regime name="integrating" initial="true"><TimeDerivative variable="w" value="(a * (v - EL) - w) / tauw"/><TimeDerivative variable="v" value="iMemb / C"/><OnCondition test="v .gt. thresh"><EventOut port="spike"/><Transition regime="refractory"/></OnCondition></Regime></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: adExIaFCell
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : lastSpikeTime (time)
State Variable : w (current)
State Variable : v (voltage)

Derived Variable : iSyn (current) = Sum[ synapses[*]/i ]
Derived Variable : iMemb (current) = -1 * gL * (v - EL) + gL * delT * exp((v - VT) / delT) - w + iSyn

On Start
  v = EL
  w = 0

Regime : refractory
  Time Derivative : dw/dt = (a * (v - EL) - w) / tauw
  
  On Entry
    lastSpikeTime = t
    v = reset
    w = w + b

  if [ t > lastSpikeTime + refract ]
    Transition : integrating

Regime : integrating  (initial)
  Time Derivative : dw/dt = (a * (v - EL) - w) / tauw
  Time Derivative : dv/dt = iMemb / C

  if [ v > thresh ]
    Event Out : spike
    Transition : refractory
fields.description: Model based on Brette R and Gerstner W (2005) Adaptive Exponential Integrate-and-Fire Model as an Effective Description of Neuronal Activity. J Neurophysiol 94:3637-3642

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="segment" description="A segment defines the smallest unit within a possibly branching structure (_morphology_), such as a dendrite or axon. The shape is given by the _proximal_ and _distal_ points. If _proximal_ is missing, the proximal point is assumed to be the _distal_ point of the parent. _parent_ specifies the parent segment. The first segment (no _parent_) usually represents the soma. NOTE: LEMS does not yet support multicompartmental modelling, so the Dynamics here is only appropriate for single compartment modelling. "><Constant name = "LEN" value = "1m" dimension = "length"/><Child name="distal" type="distal"/><Child name="proximal" type="proximal"/><Child name="parent" type="parent"/><Exposure name="surfaceArea" dimension="area"/><Exposure name="length" dimension="length"/><Exposure name="radDist" dimension="length"/><Text name="name"/><Dynamics><DerivedVariable name="radDist" dimension="length" exposure="radDist" select="distal/radius"/><DerivedVariable name="pz" dimension="length" select="proximal/zLength"/><DerivedVariable name="px" dimension="length" select="proximal/xLength"/><DerivedVariable name="py" dimension="length" select="proximal/yLength"/><DerivedVariable name="length" dimension="length" exposure="length" value="sqrt(((dx - px) * (dx - px) + (dy - py) * (dy - py) + (dz - pz) * (dz - pz))/(LEN * LEN)) * LEN"/><DerivedVariable name="dz" dimension="length" select="distal/zLength"/><DerivedVariable name="dx" dimension="length" select="distal/xLength"/><DerivedVariable name="dy" dimension="length" select="distal/yLength"/><ConditionalDerivedVariable name="surfaceArea" dimension="area" exposure="surfaceArea"><Case condition="length .eq. 0" value="4 * radDist * radDist * 3.14159265"/><Case condition="length .gt. 0" value="2 * radDist * 3.14159265 * length"/></ConditionalDerivedVariable></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: segment
fields.description: A segment defines the smallest unit within a possibly branching structure (_morphology_), such as a dendrite or axon. The shape is given by the _proximal_ and _distal_ points. If _proximal_ is missing, the proximal point is assumed to be the _distal_ point of the parent. _parent_ specifies the parent segment. The first segment (no _parent_) usually represents the soma. NOTE: LEMS does not yet support multicompartmental modelling, so the Dynamics here is only appropriate for single compartment modelling.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="iafRefCell" extends="iafCell" description="Integrate and fire cell  with capacitance _C, _leakConductance, _leakReversal and refractory period _refract"><Parameter name="refract" dimension="time"/><Attachments name="synapses" type="basePointCurrent"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="lastSpikeTime" dimension="time"/><StateVariable name="v" dimension="voltage" exposure="v"/><DerivedVariable name="iSyn" dimension="current" exposure="iSyn" select="synapses[*]/i" reduce="add"/><DerivedVariable name="iMemb" dimension="current" exposure="iMemb" value="leakConductance * (leakReversal - v) + iSyn"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="v" value="reset"/></OnStart><Regime name="refractory"><OnEntry><StateAssignment variable="lastSpikeTime" value="t"/><StateAssignment variable="v" value="reset"/></OnEntry><OnCondition test="t .gt. lastSpikeTime + refract"><Transition regime="integrating"/></OnCondition></Regime><Regime name="integrating" initial="true"><TimeDerivative variable="v" value="iMemb / C"/><OnCondition test="v .gt. thresh"><EventOut port="spike"/><Transition regime="refractory"/></OnCondition></Regime></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: iafRefCell
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : lastSpikeTime (time)
State Variable : v (voltage)

Derived Variable : iSyn (current) = Sum[ synapses[*]/i ]
Derived Variable : iMemb (current) = leakConductance * (leakReversal - v) + iSyn

On Start
  v = reset

Regime : refractory
  On Entry
    lastSpikeTime = t
    v = reset

  if [ t > lastSpikeTime + refract ]
    Transition : integrating

Regime : integrating (initial)
  Time Derivative : dv/dt = iMemb / C

  if [ v > thresh ]
    Event Out : spike
    Transition : refractory
fields.description: Integrate and fire cell  with capacitance _C, _leakConductance, _leakReversal and refractory period _refract

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="fixedFactorConcentrationModel" extends="concentrationModel" description="Model of buffering of concentration of an ion (currently hard coded to be calcium, due to requirement for _iCa) which has a baseline level _restingConc and tends to this value with time course _decayConstant. A fixed factor _rho is used to scale the incoming current INDEPENDENTLY OF THE SIZE OF THE COMPARTMENT to produce a concentration change."><Parameter name="rho" dimension="rho_factor"/><Parameter name="restingConc" dimension="concentration"/><Parameter name="decayConstant" dimension="time"/><Requirement name="surfaceArea" dimension="area"/><Requirement name="iCa" dimension="current"/><Text name="species"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="extConcentration" dimension="concentration" exposure="extConcentration"/><StateVariable name="concentration" dimension="concentration" exposure="concentration"/><TimeDerivative variable="concentration" value="(iCa/surfaceArea) * rho - ((concentration - restingConc) / decayConstant)"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="concentration" value="initialConcentration"/><StateAssignment variable="extConcentration" value="initialExtConcentration"/></OnStart><OnCondition test="concentration .lt. 0"><StateAssignment variable="concentration" value="0"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>

fields.description: Model of buffering of concentration of an ion (currently hard coded to be calcium, due to requirement for _iCa) which has a baseline level _restingConc and tends to this value with time course _decayConstant. A fixed factor _rho is used to scale the incoming current INDEPENDENTLY OF THE SIZE OF THE COMPARTMENT to produce a concentration change.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="izhikevichCell" extends="baseCellMembPot" description="Cell based on the model of Izhikevich, see http://izhikevich.org/publications/spikes.htm"><Parameter name="a" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="c" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="b" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="d" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="v0" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="thresh" dimension="voltage"/><Constant name = "MVOLT" value = "1mV" dimension = "voltage"/><Constant name = "MSEC" value = "1ms" dimension = "time"/><Attachments name="synapses" type="basePointCurrentDL"/><Exposure name="U" dimension="none"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="U" dimension="none" exposure="U"/><StateVariable name="v" dimension="voltage" exposure="v"/><DerivedVariable name="ISyn" dimension="none" select="synapses[*]/I" reduce="add"/><TimeDerivative variable="U" value="a * (b * v / MVOLT - U) / MSEC"/><TimeDerivative variable="v" value="(0.04 * v^2 / MVOLT + 5 * v + (140.0 - U + ISyn) * MVOLT)/MSEC"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="v" value="v0"/><StateAssignment variable="U" value="v0 * b / MVOLT"/></OnStart><OnCondition test="v .gt. thresh"><StateAssignment variable="v" value="c * MVOLT"/><StateAssignment variable="U" value="U + d"/><EventOut port="spike"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: izhikevichCell
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : U
State Variable : v (voltage)

Derived Variable : ISyn = Sum[ synapses[*]/I ]

Time Derivative : dU/dt = a * (b * v / MVOLT - U) / MSEC
Time Derivative : dv/dt = (0.04 * v^2 / MVOLT + 5 * v + (140.0 - U + ISyn) * MVOLT)/MSEC

On Start
  v = v0
  U = v0 * b / MVOLT

if [ v > thresh ]
  v = c * MVOLT
  U = U + d
  EventOut : spike
fields.description: Cell based on the model of Izhikevich, see http://izhikevich.org/publications/spikes.htm

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="gateHHrates" extends="baseGate" description="Gate which follows the general Hodgkin Huxley formalism"><Child name="notes" type="notes"/><Child name="forwardRate" type="baseVoltageDepRate"/><Child name="q10Settings" type="baseQ10Settings"/><Child name="reverseRate" type="baseVoltageDepRate"/><Exposure name="alpha" dimension="per_time"/><Exposure name="beta" dimension="per_time"/><Exposure name="rateScale" dimension="none"/><Exposure name="inf" dimension="none"/><Exposure name="tau" dimension="time"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="q" dimension="none" exposure="q"/><DerivedVariable name="tau" dimension="time" exposure="tau" value="1/((alpha+beta) * rateScale)"/><DerivedVariable name="fcond" dimension="none" exposure="fcond" value="q^instances"/><DerivedVariable name="rateScale" dimension="none" exposure="rateScale" select="q10Settings/q10" reduce="multiply" required="false"/><DerivedVariable name="beta" dimension="per_time" exposure="beta" select="reverseRate/r"/><DerivedVariable name="alpha" dimension="per_time" exposure="alpha" select="forwardRate/r"/><DerivedVariable name="inf" dimension="none" exposure="inf" value="alpha/(alpha+beta)"/><TimeDerivative variable="q" value="(inf - q) / tau"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="q" value="inf"/></OnStart></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: gateHHrates
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable : q

DerivedVariable : tau (time) = 1/((alpha+beta) * rateScale)
DerivedVariable : fcond = q^instances
DerivedVariable : rateScale = Prod[ q10Settings/q10 ]
DerivedVariable : beta (per_time) = reverseRate/r
DerivedVariable : alpha (per_time) = forwardRate/r
DerivedVariable : inf = alpha/(alpha+beta)

TimeDerivative dq/dt = (inf - q) / tau

On Start
  q = inf
fields.description: Gate which follows the general Hodgkin Huxley formalism

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="vHalfTransition" extends="KSTransition" description="Transition which specifies both the forward and reverse rates of transition"><Parameter name="vHalf" dimension="voltage"/><Parameter name="tau" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="z" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="gamma" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="tauMin" dimension="time"/><Constant name = "kte" value = "25.3mV" dimension = "voltage"/><Requirement name="v" dimension="voltage"/><Dynamics><DerivedVariable name="rf" dimension="per_time" exposure="rf" value="1 / (1/rf0 + tauMin)"/><DerivedVariable name="rf0" dimension="per_time" value="exp(z * gamma * (v - vHalf) / kte) / tau"/><DerivedVariable name="rr" dimension="per_time" exposure="rr" value="1 / (1/rr0 + tauMin)"/><DerivedVariable name="rr0" dimension="per_time" value="exp(-z * (1 - gamma) * (v - vHalf) / kte) / tau"/></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: vHalfTransition
fields.description: Transition which specifies both the forward and reverse rates of transition

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="HHExpLinearRate" extends="baseHHRate" description="Exponential linear form for rate equation. Linear for large positive _v, exponentially decays for large negative _v."><Dynamics><DerivedVariable name="x" dimension="none" value="(v - midpoint) / scale"/><ConditionalDerivedVariable name="r" dimension="per_time" exposure="r"><Case condition="x .neq. 0" value="rate * x / (1 - exp(0 - x))"/><Case condition="x .eq. 0" value="rate"/></ConditionalDerivedVariable></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: HHExpLinearRate
fields.dynamics_text:
Derived Variable : x  = (v - midpoint) / scale

Conditional Derived Variable : r (per_time)
  if [ x != 0 ]
    r = rate * x / (1 - exp(0 - x))
  if [ x == 0 ]
    r = rate
fields.description: Exponential linear form for rate equation. Linear for large positive _v, exponentially decays for large negative _v.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="spikeGeneratorRandom" extends="baseSpikeSource" description="Generator of spikes with a random interspike interval of at least _minISI and at most _maxISI"><Parameter name="minISI" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="maxISI" dimension="time"/><Constant name = "MSEC" value = "1ms" dimension = "time"/><Exposure name="isi" dimension="time" description = "The interval until the next spike"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="isi" dimension="time" exposure="isi"/><StateVariable name="tsince" dimension="time" exposure="tsince"/><TimeDerivative variable="tsince" value="1"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="tsince" value="0"/><StateAssignment variable="isi" value="minISI + MSEC * random((maxISI - minISI) / MSEC)"/></OnStart><OnCondition test="tsince .geq. isi"><StateAssignment variable="isi" value="minISI + MSEC * random((maxISI - minISI) / MSEC)"/><StateAssignment variable="tsince" value="0"/><EventOut port="spike"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: spikeGeneratorRandom
fields.description: Generator of spikes with a random interspike interval of at least _minISI and at most _maxISI

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="sineGenerator" extends="basePointCurrent" description="Generates a sinusoidally varying current after a time _delay, for a fixed _duration. The _period and maximum _amplitude of the current can be set as well as the _phase at which to start."><Parameter name="phase" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="delay" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="duration" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="period" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="amplitude" dimension="current"/><EventPort name="in" direction="in"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i"/><OnEvent port="in"/><OnCondition test="t .lt. delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="0"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. delay .and. t .lt. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="amplitude * sin(phase + (2 * 3.14159265 * (t-delay)/period) )"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="0"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: sineGenerator
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable i (current)

OnEvent [ in ]

  if [ t < delay ]
    i =0

  if [ t >= delay and t < duration+delay ]
    i = amplitude * sin(phase + (2 * 3.14159265 * (t-delay)/period) )

  if [ t >= duration+delay]
    i = 0
fields.description: Generates a sinusoidally varying current after a time _delay, for a fixed _duration. The _period and maximum _amplitude of the current can be set as well as the _phase at which to start.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="rampGeneratorDL" extends="basePointCurrentDL" description="Generates a ramping current after a time _delay, for a fixed _duration. During this time the dimensionless current steadily changes from _startAmplitude to _finishAmplitude."><Parameter name="delay" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="duration" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="baselineAmplitude" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="startAmplitude" dimension="none"/><Parameter name="finishAmplitude" dimension="none"/><EventPort name="in" direction="in"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="I" dimension="none" exposure="I"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="I" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"/><OnCondition test="t .lt. delay"><StateAssignment variable="I" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. delay .and. t .lt. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="I" value="startAmplitude + (finishAmplitude - startAmplitude) * (t - delay) / (duration)"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="I" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: rampGeneratorDL
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable : I

OnStart
  I = baselineAmplitude

OnEvent[ in ]
  if[ t < delay ]
    I = baselineAmplitude

  if[ t >= delay and t < duration+delay ]
    I = startAmplitude + (finishAmplitude - startAmplitude) * (t - delay) / (duration)

  if[ t >= duration+delay ]
    I = baselineAmplitude
fields.description: Generates a ramping current after a time _delay, for a fixed _duration. During this time the dimensionless current steadily changes from _startAmplitude to _finishAmplitude.

During this time the current steadily changes from _startAmplitude to _finishAmplitude."><Parameter name="delay" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="duration" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="baselineAmplitude" dimension="current"/><Parameter name="startAmplitude" dimension="current"/><Parameter name="finishAmplitude" dimension="current"/><EventPort name="in" direction="in"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="i" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"/><OnCondition test="t .lt. delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. delay .and. t .lt. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="startAmplitude + (finishAmplitude - startAmplitude) * (t - delay) / (duration)"/></OnCondition><OnCondition test="t .geq. duration+delay"><StateAssignment variable="i" value="baselineAmplitude"/></OnCondition></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: rampGenerator
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : i (current)

On Start:
  i = baselineAmplitude

OnEvent [in]
  if [ t < delay ]
    i = baselineAmplitude

  if [ t >= delay and t < duration+delay ]
    i = startAmplitude + (finishAmplitude - startAmplitude) * (t - delay) / (duration)
  
  if [ t >= duration+delay ]
    i = baselineAmplitude

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="blockingPlasticSynapse" extends="expTwoSynapse" description="Biexponential synapse that allows for     optional block and plasticity     mechanisms, which can be expressed as     child elements."><Child name="plasticityMechanism" type="basePlasticityMechanism"/><Child name="blockMechanism" type="baseBlockMechanism"/><EventPort name="relay" direction="out" description = "Used to relay incoming spikes to child plasticity mechanism"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="A" dimension="none"/><StateVariable name="B" dimension="none"/><DerivedVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i" value="g * (erev - v)"/><DerivedVariable name="plasticityFactor" dimension="none" select="plasticityMechanism/plasticityFactor" reduce="multiply" required="false"/><DerivedVariable name="g" dimension="conductance" exposure="g" value="blockFactor * gbase * (B - A)"/><DerivedVariable name="blockFactor" dimension="none" select="blockMechanism/blockFactor" reduce="multiply" required="false"/><TimeDerivative variable="A" value="-A / tauRise"/><TimeDerivative variable="B" value="-B / tauDecay"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="A" value="0"/><StateAssignment variable="B" value="0"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"><StateAssignment variable="A" value="A + plasticityFactor * waveformFactor"/><StateAssignment variable="B" value="B + plasticityFactor * waveformFactor"/><EventOut port="relay"/></OnEvent></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: blockingPlasticSynapse
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : A
State Variable : B

Derived Variable : i (current) = g * (erev - v)
Derived Variable : plasticityFactor = Prod[ plasticityMechanism/plasticityFactor ]
Derived Variable : g (conductance) = blockFactor * gbase * (B - A)
Derived Variable : blockFactor = Prod[ blockMechanism/blockFactor ]

Time Derivative : A = -A / tauRise
Time Derivative : B = -B / tauDecay

On Start
  A = 0
  B = 0

OnEvent [in]
  A = A + plasticityFactor * waveformFactor
  B = B + plasticityFactor * waveformFactor
  Event Out : relay
fields.description: Biexponential synapse that allows for     optional block and plasticity     mechanisms, which can be expressed as     child elements.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="tsodyksMarkramDepMechanism" extends="basePlasticityMechanism" description="Depression-only Tsodyks-Markram model, as in Tsodyks and Markram 1997."><Parameter name="tauRec" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="initReleaseProb" dimension="none"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="R" dimension="none"/><DerivedVariable name="U" dimension="none" value="initReleaseProb"/><DerivedVariable name="plasticityFactor" dimension="none" exposure="plasticityFactor" value="R * U"/><TimeDerivative variable="R" value="(1 - R) / tauRec"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="R" value="1"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"><StateAssignment variable="R" value="R * (1 - U)"/></OnEvent></Dynamics><Structure><With  instance="parent" as="a"/><With  instance="this" as="b"/><EventConnection from="a" to="b"/></Structure></ComponentType>
fields.name: tsodyksMarkramDepMechanism
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable : R

DerivedVariable : U = initReleaseProb
DerivedVariable : plasticityFactor = R * U

TimeDerivative : dR/dt = (1 - R) / tauRec

OnStart :
    R = 1

OnEvent [ in ] :
    R = R * (1 - U)
fields.description: Depression-only Tsodyks-Markram model, as in Tsodyks and Markram 1997.

fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : A
State Variable : P
State Variable : tsince (time)
State Variable : B
State Variable : M

Derived Variable : i (current) = g * (erev - v)
Derived Variable : g (conductance) = gbase * (B - A)

Time Derivative : A = -A / tauRise
Time Derivative : B = -B / tauDecay
Time Derivative : tsince = tsinceRate

On Start
  A = 0
  B = 0
  M = 1
  P = 1
  tsince = longTime

OnEvent [in]
  A = A + waveformFactor
  B = B + waveformFactor
  tsince = 0

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="tsodyksMarkramDepFacMechanism" extends="basePlasticityMechanism" description="Full Tsodyks-Markram STP model with both depression and facilitation, as in Tsodyks, Pawelzik and Markram 1998."><Parameter name="tauFac" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="tauRec" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="initReleaseProb" dimension="none"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="R" dimension="none"/><StateVariable name="U" dimension="none"/><DerivedVariable name="plasticityFactor" dimension="none" exposure="plasticityFactor" value="R * U"/><TimeDerivative variable="R" value="(1 - R) / tauRec"/><TimeDerivative variable="U" value="(initReleaseProb - U) / tauFac"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="R" value="1"/><StateAssignment variable="U" value="initReleaseProb"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"><StateAssignment variable="R" value="R * (1 - U)"/><StateAssignment variable="U" value="U + initReleaseProb * (1 - U)"/></OnEvent></Dynamics><Structure><With  instance="parent" as="a"/><With  instance="this" as="b"/><EventConnection from="a" to="b"/></Structure></ComponentType>
fields.name: tsodyksMarkramDepFacMechanism
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable : R
StateVariable : U

DerivedVariable : plasticityFactor = R * U

TimeDerivative : dR/dt = (1 - R) / tauRec
TimeDerivative : dU/dt = (initReleaseProb - U) / tauFac

OnStart :
    R = 1
    U = initReleaseProb

OnEvent [in] :
    R = R * (1 - U)
    U = U + initReleaseProb * (1 - U)
fields.description: Full Tsodyks-Markram STP model with both depression and facilitation, as in Tsodyks, Pawelzik and Markram 1998.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="voltageConcDepBlockMechanism" extends="baseBlockMechanism" description="Synaptic blocking mechanism which varys with membrane potential across the synapse, e.g. in NMDA receptor mediated synapses"><Parameter name="scalingConc" dimension="concentration"/><Parameter name="blockConcentration" dimension="concentration"/><Parameter name="scalingVolt" dimension="voltage"/><Requirement name="v" dimension="voltage"/><Text name="species"/><Dynamics><DerivedVariable name="blockFactor" dimension="none" exposure="blockFactor" value="1/(1 + (blockConcentration / scalingConc)* exp(-1 * (v / scalingVolt)))"/></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: voltageConcDepBlockMechanism
fields.dynamics_text: DerivedVariable : blockFactor = 1/(1 + (blockConcentration / scalingConc)* exp(-1 * (v / scalingVolt)))
fields.description: Synaptic blocking mechanism which varys with membrane potential across the synapse, e.g. in NMDA receptor mediated synapses

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="expTwoSynapse" extends="baseConductanceBasedSynapse" description="Ohmic synapse model whose conductance waveform on receiving an event has a rise time of _tauRise and a decay time of _tauDecay. Max conductance reached during this time (assuming zero conductance before) is _gbase."><Parameter name="tauDecay" dimension="time"/><Parameter name="tauRise" dimension="time"/><DerivedParameter name="waveformFactor" dimension="none" value="1 / (-exp(-peakTime / tauRise) + exp(-peakTime / tauDecay))"/><DerivedParameter name="peakTime" dimension="time" value="log(tauDecay / tauRise) * (tauRise * tauDecay)/(tauDecay - tauRise)"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="A" dimension="none"/><StateVariable name="B" dimension="none"/><DerivedVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i" value="g * (erev - v)"/><DerivedVariable name="g" dimension="conductance" exposure="g" value="gbase * (B - A)"/><TimeDerivative variable="A" value="-A / tauRise"/><TimeDerivative variable="B" value="-B / tauDecay"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="A" value="0"/><StateAssignment variable="B" value="0"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"><StateAssignment variable="A" value="A + waveformFactor"/><StateAssignment variable="B" value="B + waveformFactor"/></OnEvent></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: expTwoSynapse
fields.dynamics_text:
DerivedParameter : waveformFactor = 1 / (-exp(-peakTime / tauRise) + exp(-peakTime / tauDecay))
DerivedParameter : peakTime (time) = log(tauDecay / tauRise) * (tauRise * tauDecay)/(tauDecay - tauRise)

State Variable : A
State Variable : B

Derived Variable : i (current) = g * (erev - v)
Derived Variable : g (conductance) = gbase * (B - A)

Time Derivative : dA/dt = -A / tauRise
Time Derivative : dB/dt = -B / tauDecay

On Start
  A = 0
  B = 0

OnEvent [ in ]
  A = A + waveformFactor
  B = B + waveformFactor
fields.description: Ohmic synapse model whose conductance waveform on receiving an event has a rise time of _tauRise and a decay time of _tauDecay. Max conductance reached during this time (assuming zero conductance before) is _gbase.

fields.xml: <ComponentType name="expOneSynapse" extends="baseConductanceBasedSynapse" description="Ohmic synapse model whose conductance rises instantaneously by _gbase on receiving an event, and which decays exponentially to zero with time course _tauDecay"><Parameter name="tauDecay" dimension="time"/><Dynamics><StateVariable name="g" dimension="conductance" exposure="g"/><DerivedVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i" value="g * (erev - v)"/><TimeDerivative variable="g" value="-g / tauDecay"/><OnStart><StateAssignment variable="g" value="0"/></OnStart><OnEvent port="in"><StateAssignment variable="g" value="g + gbase"/></OnEvent></Dynamics></ComponentType>
fields.name: expOneSynapse
fields.dynamics_text:
State Variable : g (conductance)

Derived Variable : i (current) = g * (erev - v)

Time Derivative : dg/dt = -g / tauDecay

On Start
  g = 0

OnEvent [ in ]
  g = g + gbase
fields.description: Ohmic synapse model whose conductance rises instantaneously by _gbase on receiving an event, and which decays exponentially to zero with time course _tauDecay

<ComponentType name="baseSensoryCondBasedPointCell" extends="baseCellMembPotCap"
        description="Base type for Si elegans neurons to receive all sensory inputs">
        <Child name="notes" type="notes"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_NaCl" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_biotin" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_ethanol" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_butanone" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_SDS" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_quinine" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_benzaldehyde" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_diacetyl" dimension="concentration"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_NaN3" dimension="concentration"/>
		
        <Parameter name="sensory_temperature" dimension="temperature"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_force" dimension="none"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_stretch" dimension="none"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_flexion" dimension="none"/>
		
        <Parameter name="sensory_light_wavelength" dimension="none"/>
        <Parameter name="sensory_light_intensity" dimension="none"/>
		<Parameter name="v0" dimension="voltage"/>  <!--TEMP: needs to be removed... -->
        <Parameter name="thresh" dimension="voltage"/>

        <Children name="populations" type="baseChannelPopulation"/>

        <Attachments name="synapses" type="basePointCurrent"/>

        <Dynamics>
		

            <StateVariable name="v" exposure="v" dimension="voltage"/>
            <StateVariable name="spiking" dimension="none"/>

            <DerivedVariable name="iChannels" dimension="current" select="populations[*]/i" reduce="add"/>
            <DerivedVariable name="iSyn" dimension="current" exposure="iSyn" select="synapses[*]/i" reduce="add" />
            <DerivedVariable name="iMemb" dimension="current" exposure="iMemb" value="iChannels + iSyn"/>

            <TimeDerivative variable="v" value="iMemb / C"/>

            <OnStart>
                <StateAssignment variable="v" value="v0"/>
                <StateAssignment variable="spiking" value="0"/>
            </OnStart>

            <OnCondition test="v .gt. thresh .and. spiking .lt. 0.5">
                <StateAssignment variable="spiking" value="1"/>
                <EventOut port="spike"/>
            </OnCondition>

            <OnCondition test="v .lt. thresh">
                <StateAssignment variable="spiking" value="0"/>
            </OnCondition>

        </Dynamics>
    </ComponentType>
fields.name: baseSensoryCondBasedPointCell
fields.description: Base type for Si elegans neurons to receive all sensory inputs

<ComponentType name="temperatureSensoryChannelPopulation"
        extends="baseChannelPopulation"
        description="Population of temperature sensitive channels.">

        <Parameter name="number" dimension="none"/>

        <Parameter name="gBase" dimension="conductance"/>

            <DerivedVariable name="i" dimension="current" exposure="i" value="geff * (erev - v)"/>
        </Dynamics>

fields.xml:
<ComponentType name="gradedSynapse"
                   extends="baseGradedSynapse"
                   description="STILL IN DEVELOPMENT!!!! Based on synapse in Methods of http://www.nature.com/neuro/journal/v7/n12/abs/nn1352.html">
        
        <Parameter name="conductance" dimension="conductance"/>
        
        <Parameter name="delta" dimension="voltage" description="Slope of the activation curve"/>
        <Parameter name="k" dimension="per_time" description="Rate constant for transmitter-receptor dissociation rate"/>
        <Parameter name="Vth" dimension="voltage" description="The half-activation voltage of the synapse"/>
        <Parameter name="erev" dimension="voltage" description="The reversal potential of the synapse"/>
        
        <Exposure name="i" dimension="current"/>
        <Exposure name="inf" dimension="none"/>
        <Exposure name="tau" dimension="time"/>
        
        <Requirement name="v" dimension="voltage"/>

        <InstanceRequirement name="peer" type="gapJunction"/>

        <Dynamics>
            <StateVariable name="s" dimension="none"/>
            
            <DerivedVariable name="vpeer" dimension="voltage" select="peer/v"/>
            
            <DerivedVariable name="inf" dimension="none" value="1/(1 + exp((Vth - vpeer)/delta))" exposure="inf"/>
            <DerivedVariable name="tau" dimension="time" value="(1-inf)/k" exposure="tau"/>
            
            <DerivedVariable name="i" exposure="i"  value="conductance * s * (erev-v)"/>
            
            <!-- To catch case where tau ~ 0 => too fast a change in s => numerical instability -->
            <ConditionalDerivedVariable name="s_rate" dimension="per_time">
                <Case condition="(1-inf) .gt. 1e-4" value="(inf - s)/tau"/>
                <Case value="0"/>
            </ConditionalDerivedVariable>
            
            <TimeDerivative variable="s" value="s_rate" />
            
            <!-- To catch case where tau ~ 0 => too fast a change in s => numerical instability -->
            <OnCondition test="(1-inf) .lt. 1e-4">
                <StateAssignment variable="s" value="inf"/>
            </OnCondition>
            
        </Dynamics>
    </ComponentType>
fields.name: gradedSynapse
fields.dynamics_text:
StateVariable: s
            
DerivedVariable : vpeer (voltage) = peer/v
DerivedVariable : inf = 1/(1 + exp((Vth - vpeer)/delta))
DerivedVariable : tau (time) = (1-inf)/k
DerivedVariable : i = conductance * s * (erev-v)
            
<!-- To catch case where tau ~ 0 => too fast a change in s => numerical instability -->
ConditionalDerivedVariable : s_rate (per_time)
    Case [ (1-inf) > 1e-4 ] : srate = (inf - s)/tau
    Case [ default ] : srate = 0

TimeDerivative : ds/dt = s_rate
            
<!-- To catch case where tau ~ 0 => too fast a change in s => numerical instability -->
if [ (1-inf) < 1e-4 ] :
    s = inf
fields.description: STILL IN DEVELOPMENT!!!! Based on synapse in Methods of http://www.nature.com/neuro/journal/v7/n12/abs/nn1352.html
